# Naming & containers

## Members

- Data members use Qt-style **`m_` + camelCase**: `m_currentSkin`, `m_store`.
- Do **not** use trailing-underscore Google style (`currentSkin_`).
- Do **not** invent a second prefix (`m_foo_`).

## Functions / parameters

- Keep Qt API style: **lowerCamelCase** (`setColorScheme`, `packId`).

## Constants

- `kCamelCase` / `SettingsKeys::kSkinId` are allowed (stable string/pack ids).
- Prefer `inline constexpr` over macros.

## Containers

- **UI / signals / slots / Engine-facing APIs**: prefer Qt (`QString`, `QStringList`, `QVector`, `QHash`, …).
- **Core algorithms, wire codecs, peelable modules**: prefer STL (`std::vector`, `std::string`, …).

## Include guards

- Keep `__{TARGET}_{FILE}_H__` (see `cpp-include-guards.mdc`).
- Formatting stays in `.clang-format` (do not change for naming).
